title: For Sale:  AR-15  .223 Wylde
postcontent: For sale is my AR15 I assembled recently.  All parts on this rifle were purchased new.  The DPMS lower receiver is a few years old, but sat in my safe until I put this rifle together.  The parts list for the build is as followsCriterion 20 inch hybrid contour chambered in .223 wylde.  Rifle length gas system.  Chrome-lined and parkerized finish.Griffin Armament linear compensator.Seekins SP3R V3 15 inch handguard.Seekins IMRT-3 V3 Billet Monolithic upper.Seekins Adjustable gas block and melonited rifle length gas tube.Seekins Enhanced lower parts kit (trigger guard, mag release, bolt catch, ambi safety selector, take down pins).Bravo Company bolt carrier group.DPMS Lower receiver.Timney 3 pound AR-15 trigger (small pin).Accu wedge.Lancer Carbon fixed Stock - A2 Rifle length.Aero Precision rifle length buffer tube, rifle buffer, and buffer spring.Ergo Grip tactical deluxe pisto grip.Primary Arms 1-8x with the ACSS reticle (very nice scope)Vortex Cantilever scope mount.I had the handguard, lower, trigger guard, and dust cover cerakoted in Midnight Bronze.I have shot exactly 100 rounds with this rifle.  I have tried four different "models" of ammunition.  I shot Hornady Black 75gn BTHP, Hornady Match 73gn ELD-match, Federal Premium with 73gn Berger bullet (2 boxes of this ammo), and PPU Match 69gn match.All the tested ammo shot well except the PPU.  I had hoped the PPU would shoot good because it was the cheapest at $11 per box, but it shot like crap out of this rifle.  Groups were anywhere from 1.5 to 2 inches with the PPU ammo.  The best was Federal Premium with Berger bullets, the next best was Hornady Black followed by Hornady match. Hornady Black - Avg velocity 2654 fps with an SD of 20 fps and extreme spread of 82 fpsHornady Match - Avg velocity 2670 fps with an SD of 37.6 fps and extreme spread of 143 fps.  I really exptected the Hornady match to perform better.  I think I got a bad batch.  I literally had a dud.  Ran it through my rifle twice and nothing.  If I keep this rifle I will most likely try this ammo again just to be sure.  Groups were good, right at an inch, but the Black grouped just slightly better.Federal Premium - Avg velocity of 2676 fps with an SD of 19 fps and extreme spread of 69 fps.  I ran two boxes because the first box I messed up with the chronograph data and didn't have definitive/reliable data.  This ammo shot the best.  I had one group right at a half inch (3 shot group though).PPU Match - 2731 fps with an SD of 21.5 and an extreme spread of 82 fps.  Consisitent ammo, but consistently produced poor groups.It's a great/fun rifle but I've decided I want to build another bolt gun.  I just have a preference for bot guns.  I would like $1,000 for the rifle as described and pictured.  The magazine pictured is actually a 6.8spc magazine and not included (I used it for pictures for the Cerakoter).  I have 2 5 round magpul magazine that will be included.Any questions please let me know.Local sale only.  I will not ship.

title: For Sale:  IMI Uzi Carbine Model B 9mm Rare!!  Reduced!  Must Sell!
postcontent: This an IMI (Israeli Military Industries) UZI Carbine, Model B (upgraded sights and firing pin safety), imported by Action Arms.  These were only imported from 1983-1989, and have not been imported since.  This is actually an Israeli model, not the cheap (reliability and compatibility is hit and miss) knockoffs that are still being produced in the states.  These UZIs are easy to break down to fix and clean, and of course I will walk any buyer through how to do it all.  Because these are not made/imported any more in the US, they are just going up in value.  This is an awesome rifle...  They sell conversion kits for 45 acp, and the barrel is easily removed for stowing in a compact backpack.  This is why they are highly sought after for use as camp carbines and bugout bags.  Super reliable and easy to maintain, this is the hallmark of Israeli weapons systems.  With the rifle I have 7 - 25 round mags, the original case (one hinge is damaged, but should be easily repairable), and the barrel blank.  The rifle has very few rounds through it.  Please email me with any questions,  Must sell!Austin

title: For Sale:  ARMITAGE INTL. LTD SKORPION 9mm  Great Condition
postcontent: Skorpion Scarab 9mmThe 9x19mm Skorpion Scarab was made in South Carolina by Armitage International in 1989 and 1990, with a total of just 600 being produced. They were chasing the same market as the MAC-10, TEC-9, and similar big scary-looking pistols. In fact, the Scarab uses modified M10 magazines (an extra cut added in the top side to match with its mag catch) and is threaded for MAC barrel extensions or suppressors. The rate reducing mechanism from the vz.61 is absent (no surprise, as the Scarab is semi-auto only), and the FCG is a copy of a basic AK FCG.  The upper assembly is stamped and folded like a MAC, and the bolt is designed to be extremely simple to manufacture. Includes One 15 round magazine and a very nice Pleican Style Case.
